semantic_equivalence_artifact.original_latex_theorem:
\label{c:cones are indiscernible} Let $T$ be a meet{\hyp}tree, $\gamma$ a point, $C$ a finite subset of $T$ and $a,b$ single elements above $\gamma$. Suppose $a\notin\cone_{\gamma}(C)$ and $b\notin \cone_\gamma(C)$. Then, $\qftp_\gamma(a/C)=\qftp_\gamma(b/C)$.
\begin{proof} By \cref{l:generated}(\ref{itm:generated 4}), we have that $\langle a,C\rangle_\gamma=\langle C\rangle_\gamma\cup \{a\}$ and $\langle b,C\rangle_\gamma=\langle C\rangle_\gamma\cup\{b\}$. Furthermore, for $x\in\langle C\rangle_\gamma$, $x\leq a$ if and only if $x\leq \gamma$, if and only if $x\leq b$. Thus, by \cref{l:quantifier free type}, we conclude that $\qftp_\gamma(a/C)=\qftp_\gamma(b/C)$.
\end{proof}

