semantic_equivalence_artifact.original_latex_theorem:
\label{c:semibranch intervals are indiscernible}
Let $T$ be a meet{\hyp}tree, $\Gamma$ a semibranch, $C$ a finite subset of $T$ and $a,b$ single elements in $\Gamma$. Write $\pi(C)=\{\pi_{\Gamma}(c)\tq c\in C\}$. Then, $\qftp_\Gamma(a/C)=\qftp_\Gamma(b/C)$ if and only if $\qftp_{<}(a/\pi(C))=\qftp_{<}(b/\pi(C))$.
\begin{proof} The ``only if'' implication is obvious, let's prove the ``if'' one. Set $\bar{C}=\langle C\rangle_{\Gamma}$. By \cref{l:generated}(\ref{itm:generated 7}), $\langle a\, C\rangle_\Gamma=\bar{C}\cup \{a\}$ and $\langle b\, C\rangle_\Gamma=\bar{C}\cup \{b\}$. By \cref{l:quantifier free type}, $\qftp_\Gamma(b/C)=\qftp_\Gamma(a/C)$ if and only if $\qftp_{<}(b/\bar{C})=\qftp_{<}(a/\bar{C})$. Pick $c\in\bar{C}$ arbitrary. If $c\leq a$, then $c\in \Gamma$ so, by \cref{l:generated}(\ref{itm:generated 6}), $c\in\pi(C)$ and, by hypothesis, $c\leq b$. If $a\leq c$, as $a\in \Gamma$, then $a\leq \pi_{\Gamma}(c)\leq c$ and, by \cref{l:generated}(\ref{itm:generated 6}), $\pi_{\Gamma}(c)\in \pi(C)$, so $b\leq \pi_{\Gamma}(c)\leq c$ by hypothesis. Symmetrically, $c\leq b$ implies $c\leq a$ and $b\leq c$ implies $a\leq c$.
\end{proof}

