\label{l:no based cone-independence definition}
Let $T$ be a meet{\hyp}tree and $A,B,C$ subsets of $T$. Then, $A\indepe[\gamma]{C}B$ for some $\gamma\in C$ if and only if $A\indepe[\gamma]{C}B$ for any $\gamma\in C$.
\begin{proof} It is enough to note that, for $\gamma\in C$, we have $\langle AC\rangle_\gamma=\langle AC\rangle_\wedge$, $\langle BC\rangle_\gamma=\langle BC\rangle_\wedge$ and $\langle C\rangle_\gamma=\langle C\rangle_\wedge$ by \cref{l:generated}(\ref{itm:generated 1}). Thus, the \cref{d:cone-independence} of $A\indepe[\gamma]{C}B$ is independent of $\gamma$ when $\gamma\in C$.
\end{proof}

