\label{l:semibranched independence in substructures} Let $(T_1,\Gamma_1)$ be a semibranched meet{\hyp}tree and $(T_2,\Gamma_2)$ a substructure of $(T_1,\Gamma_1)$ as semibranched meet{\hyp}tree. Then, for any $A,B,C\subseteq T_2$, $A\indepe[\Gamma_2]{C}B$ if and only if $A\indepe[\Gamma_1]{C}B$. 
\begin{proof} For $x\in X\subseteq T_2$, $\pi_{\Gamma_2}(x)=\pi_{\Gamma_1}(x)$ and $\langle X\rangle_{\Gamma_2}=\langle X\rangle_{\Gamma_1}$. Therefore, the definitions of $\indepe[\Gamma_1]{}$ and $\indepe[\Gamma_2]{}$ agree on subsets of $T_2$. 
\end{proof}

