\item By recursion hypothesis {\rm{(iii,iv)}}, $\alpha^{-1}(a_{-n})<a_{-n}=\min X_n\cap\Gamma^{\circ}$. Hence, by \cref{l:saturation of increasing points}(\ref{itm:saturation of increasing points 2}), we can find $b'\in \Gamma^{\circ}$ such that $\alpha^{-1}(a_{-n})c_{n+1}a_n\bar{x}\equiv^{\Rr\Gamma} b'\alpha(b)b\bar{y}$ with $\alpha(b')>b'$ and $b'<\pi_{\Gamma}(w_n)$. 
\item Then, $\alpha^{-1}(b')<b'$, so, applying \cref{l:saturation of increasing points}(\ref{itm:saturation of increasing points 2}) again, we can find $a_{-n-1}\in \Gamma^{\circ}$ such that $a_{-n-1}\alpha^{-1}(a_{-n})c_{n+1}a_n\bar{x}\equiv^{\Rr\Gamma}\alpha^{-1}(b')b'\alpha(b)b\bar{y}$ with $\alpha(a_{-n-1})>a_{-n-1}$ and $a_{-n-1}<\pi_{\Gamma}(w_{n})$. 
