\item By recursion hypothesis {\rm{(iv)}}, we know that $c'_n=\min X_n\cap\Gamma^{\circ}$ where $c'_n=\beta_n^{-1}\alpha\beta_n(a'_{n-1})$. Set $a'_n=\alpha(c'_n)$. By recursion hypothesis {\rm{(iii)}}, $a'_n=\alpha(c'_n)<c'_n$. Hence, by \cref{l:saturation of increasing points}(\ref{itm:saturation of increasing points 2}) applied to $\alpha^{-1}$, we can find $b'\in\Gamma^\circ$ such that $a'_nc_{n+1}a_n\bar{x}\equiv^{\Rr\Gamma} b'\alpha(b)b\bar{y}$ with $\alpha(b')<b'$ and $b'<\pi_{\Gamma}(w_n)$.
\item Applying \cref{l:saturation of increasing points}(\ref{itm:saturation of increasing points 2}) to $\alpha^{-1}$ again, we can find $c'_{n+1}\in\Gamma^{\circ}$ with $\alpha(c'_{n+1})<c'_{n+1}$ and $c'_{n+1}<\pi_{\Gamma}(w_{n})$ such that $c'_{n+1}a'_nc_{n+1}a_n\bar{x}\equiv^{\Rr\Gamma}\alpha(b')b'\alpha(b)b\bar{y}$.
